  }, "Ethan Zuckerman:")), mdx("p", null, "Welcome everybody back to Reimagining the Internet. I'm your host, Ethan Zuckerman. We are here today with Julia Angwin, one of my favorite people in the world. An incredible investigative journalist. She's worked with the Wall Street Journal. She worked for quite some time with ProPublica. She is co-founder of a wonderful project called The Markup. We're going to talk about how investigative journalism can help us understand what's going on with social media and what might be wrong with it. Julia, thanks so much for joining us."), mdx("p", null, mdx("em", {
